This article is a statement made by President Obama in response to the report of the Senate Select Committee on Intelligence regarding the CIA's detention and interrogation program following the 9/11 attacks. The President acknowledges the sacrifices made by the intelligence community and the importance of their work in keeping the country safe. However, he also expresses his belief that some of the actions taken during this program were contrary to American values and banned torture when he took office. The President states that these harsh methods were not effective in counterterrorism efforts and damaged America's reputation internationally. He pledges to use his authority as President to ensure that these methods are not used again. The President emphasizes the importance of staying true to American ideals and acknowledges that the nation is not perfect but is willing to confront its past and make changes. He concludes by affirming that the United States will continue to fight against terrorism and remain a force for freedom and human dignity in the world.